데이터 추가

total_df = df %>% 
            mutate(is_prt = (country == "PRT"),
                   headcount = (adults+children+babies),
                   total_stays_night = stays_in_weekend_nights+ stays_in_week_nights)

head(total_df)

resort_df = total_df %>% filter(hotel == "Resort Hotel")
city_df = total_df %>% filter(hotel == "City Hotel")
resort_client = resort_df %>% select(adults, children, babies, customer_type, is_prt, headcount)

resort_reservation_pattern = resort_df %>% select(is_canceled, lead_time, is_repeated_guest, previous_cancellations, previous_bookings_not_canceled, booking_changes, deposit_type, days_in_waiting_list, adr, required_car_parking_spaces, total_of_special_requests, reservation_status) # reservation_status_date

resort_lodgment = resort_df %>% select(arrival_date_year, arrival_date_month, arrival_date_week_number, total_stays_night, arrival_date_day_of_month, stays_in_weekend_nights, stays_in_week_nights, reserved_room_type, assigned_room_type, meal)

resort_reservation_route = resort_df %>% select(distribution_channel, market_segment)

사용하는 시각화용 함수들

# 계수 시각화 
make_coef_heatmap = function(matrix){
    coef <- as.data.frame(matrix)
    coef$rownames <- rownames(coef)
    coef <- as.data.frame(coef)
    
    # 데이터프레임 melt
    coef_long <- melt(coef, id.vars = "rownames")
    
    # heatmap 그리기
    ggplot(coef_long, aes(x = variable, y = rownames, fill = value)) +
      geom_tile() +
      geom_text(aes(label = round(value, 2)), color = "black", size = 4) +
      scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", midpoint = 0) +
      theme_minimal() +
      labs(x = "Variable", y = "Rowname", fill = "Coefficient") +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
}

# 상관계수 행렬 시각화 
make_corr_heatmap = function(matrix){
    corr <- as.data.frame(matrix)
    corr$rownames <- rownames(corr)
    corr <- as.data.frame(corr)
    
    # 데이터프레임 melt
    corr_long <- melt(corr, id.vars = "rownames")
    
    # heatmap 그리기
    ggplot(corr_long, aes(x = variable, y = rownames, fill = value)) +
      geom_tile() +
      geom_text(aes(label = round(value, 2)), color = "black", size = 4) +
      scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", midpoint = 0, limits = c(-1, 1)) +
      theme_minimal() +
      labs(x = "Variable", y = "Rowname", fill = "Correlation") +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
}

  return((x - mean(x)) / sd(x))
}

                                  mutate(lead_time = normalize(lead_time),
